l need to check if I should qualify the class path. I also need to verify that the constructor for `ForJava7CapableVm` can be called from the subclass. Then, I'll want to ensure I handle locks properly, particularly regarding the class loading lock behavior for parallel capabilities.\"},{\"type\":\"summary_text\",\"text\":\"**Analyzing parallel capability in ClassLoader**\\n\\nI'm examining whether `ByteArrayClassLoader` registers as parallel capable by invoking `doRegisterAsParallelCapable`. If it is indeed parallel capable, it returns a per-class object. However, I can't assert that the same lock will be stable since names might differ. It's crucial to note that the specification suggests that the same class name should return the same lock. I need to consider this behavior carefully to ensure I'm complying with the ClassLoader specifications.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_QRsOiWKA4U6zFVqLMUmMYPn3|fc_06683b30337ae7a1016a29ae4bed0c8193b621e9f31ff36cf9", "name": "write", "arguments": {"path": "tests/src/io.projectreactor.tools/blockhound/1.0.8.RELEASE/src/test/java/io_projectreactor_tools/blockhound/ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerSynchronizationStrategyInnerForJava7CapableVmTest.java", "content": "/*\n * Copyright and related rights waived via CC0\n *\n * You should have received a copy of the CC0 legalcode along with this\n * work. If not, see <http://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/>.\n */\npackage io_projectreactor_tools.blockhound;\n\nimport org.junit.jupiter.api.Test;\nimport reactor.blockhound.shaded.net.bytebuddy.dynamic.loading.ByteArrayClassLoader;\n\nimport java.lang.reflect.Method;\nimport java.util.Collections;\n\nimport static org.assertj.core.api.Assertions.assertThat;\n\npublic class ByteArrayClassLoaderInnerSynchronizationStrategyInnerForJava7CapableVmTest {\n    @Test\n    void java7SynchronizationStrategyUsesClassLoaderLockLookup() throws Exception {\n        try {\n            Java7CapableByteArrayClassLoader classLoader = new Java7CapableByteArrayClassLoader(\n                    getClass().getClassLoader());\n\n            Object firstLock = classLoader.getLockFor(\"io_projectreactor_tools.blockhound.generated.LockedType\");\n            Object secondLock = classLoader.getLockFor(\"io_projectreactor_tools.blockhound.generated.LockedType\");\n\n            assertThat(firstLock).isNotNull();\n            assertThat(secondLock).isSameAs(firstLock);\n        } catch (Throwable throwable) {\n            BlockHoundNativeImageSupport.rethrowIfNotExpectedNativeImageFailure(throwable);\n        }\n    }\n}\n\nfinal class Java7CapableByteArrayClassLoader extends ByteArrayClassLoader {\n    Java7CapableByteArrayClassLoader(ClassLoader parent) {\n        super(parent, false, Collections.emptyMap());\n    }\n\n    Object getLockFor(String name) throws Exception {\n        Method getClassLoadingLock = ClassLoader.class.getDeclaredMethod(\"getClassLoadingLock\", String.class);\n        SynchronizationStrategy strategy = new Java7SynchronizationStrategy(getClassLoadingLock).initialize();\n        return strategy.getClassLoadingLock(this, name);\n    }\n\n    private final class Java7SynchronizationStrategy extends SynchronizationStrategy.ForJava7CapableVm {\n        private Java7SynchronizationStrategy(Method method) {\n            super(method);\n        }\n    }\n}\n"}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "oca/gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1902, "output": 1593, "cacheRead": 43008, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 46503, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1781116464188, "responseId": "resp_06683b30337ae7a1016a29ae311ccc8193ac42a2bc0fc513f4"}}
